@startuml
!include ../../images/common-sequence.iuml

title Processor Crash Recovery & Backlog Replay

box "Host A — Receiver" $OnPrem
    participant "Receiver" as Receiver
end box

box "Host B — Central Server" $OnPrem
    queue "RabbitMQ\n(adsb-{n} / archive)" as MQ
    participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTT
end box

box "Host C — Processor" $OnPrem
    participant "Processor" as Proc
    database "active_flights.db" as ActiveDB
    database "completed_flights.db" as FallbackDB
end box

== Normal operation ==

Receiver -> MQ++ : **Publish**\n""adsb-{n}""\n""{raw, icao_hex, received_at, source}""
MQ -> Proc++ : **Consume**
Proc -> ActiveDB : **Save flight** (commit)\nflight_id assigned on first message
Proc -> Proc : message_clock = max(message_clock, received_at)

opt Rule matched
    alt lag = now - received_at <= rule_notification_max_lag_seconds
        Proc -> MQTT-- : **Publish**\n""SkyFollower/rule/{identifier}""
    else lag > rule_notification_max_lag_seconds
        Proc -> Proc : **Suppress** — log debug\n(icao_hex, rule identifier, lag)
    end
end

== Processor goes down (crash or deliberate stop — handled identically) ==

note over Proc
    SIGKILL / OOM-kill / ""docker kill"" / SIGTERM
    No special shutdown path — see #459
end note

Receiver -> MQ : **Publish** (still up)
note over MQ
    Messages accumulate in the durable
    ""adsb-{n}"" queue while Processor is down
end note

== RabbitMQ itself also unavailable (independent failure) ==

Receiver -> Receiver : **Write to** ""queue.db"" (SQLite WAL)
Receiver -> MQ : **Drain** ""queue.db"" once RabbitMQ reachable again

== Processor restarts ==

Proc -> ActiveDB++ : **Reopen** ""active_flights.db""
ActiveDB --> Proc-- : recovered flight rows
Proc -> Proc : message_clock = MAX(last_message) over recovered rows\n(or now() if store was empty)
note right of Proc
    Recovered flights are **not** archived
    on wall-clock time alone
end note
Proc -> MQ++ : **Reconnect**, resume consuming ""adsb-{n}""

== Backlog replay ==

loop for each backlog message
    MQ -> Proc : **Consume**\n""received_at"" = historical timestamp
    Proc -> Proc : message_clock = max(message_clock, received_at)

    alt existing flight AND (received_at - last_message) > flight_ttl_seconds
        Proc -> FallbackDB : **Archive** prior flight (reuses stored flight_id)\n(or publish to ""archive"" queue if RabbitMQ up)
        Proc -> ActiveDB : **Delete** old row (commit)
        Proc -> ActiveDB : **Insert** new flight, new flight_id (commit)
    else continues existing flight
        Proc -> ActiveDB : **Append** position/velocity (commit)
    end

    opt Rule matched
        alt lag <= rule_notification_max_lag_seconds
            Proc -> MQTT : **Publish** rule notification
        else lag > rule_notification_max_lag_seconds
            Proc -> Proc : **Suppress** — log debug
        end
    end
end

== Caught up to live traffic ==

note over Proc
    message_clock ≈ wall clock again;
    rule notifications resume normally
end note

== Periodic eviction (message-clock gated) ==

Proc -> ActiveDB++ : **Select** WHERE last_message < message_clock - flight_ttl_seconds
ActiveDB --> Proc-- : stale icao_hex list
Proc -> FallbackDB : **Archive** each stale flight (reuses stored flight_id)
Proc -> ActiveDB : **Delete** (commit)

@enduml
